# shadcn/ui Component Library

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for ALL UI elements. shadcn/ui is a collection of re-usable components built with Radix UI and Tailwind CSS.

## CRITICAL RULE: NO CUSTOM UI COMPONENTS

**ABSOLUTELY NO CUSTOM UI COMPONENTS ARE ALLOWED IN THIS PROJECT.**

- **ONLY** shadcn/ui components may be used for any UI elements
- **NEVER** create custom UI components from scratch
- **NEVER** build custom buttons, cards, inputs, modals, or any other UI elements
- **ALWAYS** use shadcn/ui components for all UI needs
- If a component doesn't exist in shadcn/ui, install it using `npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>`
- Components can be customized by editing the shadcn/ui component files directly in `components/ui/`

## Clerk Authentication UI Requirements

**Clerk sign in and sign up functionality MUST follow these requirements:**

1. **Sign In/Sign Up Buttons**: 
   - **MUST** use shadcn/ui `Button` component from `@/components/ui/button`
   - **NEVER** use Clerk's default button components or create custom buttons
   - Example: `<Button onClick={() => setSignInOpen(true)}>Sign In</Button>`

2. **Modal Implementation**:
   - **MUST** use shadcn/ui `Dialog` component for sign in and sign up modals
   - Install with: `npx shadcn@latest add dialog`
   - Clerk's authentication forms should be rendered inside the shadcn/ui Dialog component
   - **NEVER** use Clerk's built-in modal or page-based authentication UI
   - Example structure:
     ```tsx
     <Dialog open={signInOpen} onOpenChange={setSignInOpen}>
       <DialogContent>
         <SignIn />
       </DialogContent>
     </Dialog>
     ```

3. **Integration Pattern**:
   - Use Clerk's `<SignIn />` and `<SignUp />` components inside shadcn/ui Dialog components
   - Trigger the dialogs using shadcn/ui Button components
   - Maintain consistent UI styling by using only shadcn/ui components

## Initialization

If shadcn/ui is not initialized in the project, use the following command:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

This will:
- Set up the necessary configuration files
- Configure Tailwind CSS
- Set up the components directory structure
- Install required dependencies

## Installing Components

If a particular component is not installed, use the following command to add it:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

For example, to install the button component:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Common components you may need:
- `button` - For all buttons including Clerk authentication triggers
- `dialog` - For modals including Clerk sign in/sign up
- `card` - For card layouts
- `input` - For form inputs
- `form` - For form handling

## Usage Guidelines

- **ONLY** use shadcn/ui components for UI elements - no exceptions
- Components are installed in the `components/ui` directory
- Import components from `@/components/ui/<component-name>`
- Components can be customized by editing the component files directly in `components/ui/`
- Check the [shadcn/ui documentation](https://ui.shadcn.com) for available components and their usage
- Before creating any UI element, check if a shadcn/ui component exists for it
- If a component doesn't exist, install it rather than creating a custom one

## Dark Mode Requirements

This project is in **dark mode**. When customizing or using shadcn/ui components, ensure proper contrast:

- **NEVER** use dark colored text on dark backgrounds
- **NEVER** use light colored text on light backgrounds
- **ALWAYS** ensure sufficient contrast between text and background colors
- Use Tailwind's dark mode classes appropriately (e.g., `dark:text-white`, `dark:bg-gray-900`)
- When customizing component styles, test in dark mode to verify readability
- shadcn/ui components are designed to work with dark mode by default, but customizations must maintain proper contrast
